{"award_age":58.0,"bio_image":"full\/ab3949c676474de324113b5d2e23a1a33e11a06d.jpg","category":"Economics","country":"United States","date_of_birth":"1943-02-09T00:00:00.000Z","date_of_death":null,"gender":"male","image_urls":["http:\/\/upload.wikimedia.org\/wikipedia\/commons\/thumb\/8\/84\/Joseph_E._Stiglitz_-_cropped.jpg\/220px-Joseph_E._Stiglitz_-_cropped.jpg"],"link":"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Joseph_E._Stiglitz","mini_bio":"<p><b>Joseph Eugene <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Stieglitz_(surname)\" title=\"Stieglitz (surname)\">Stiglitz<\/a><\/b>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Foreign_Member_of_the_Royal_Society\" title=\"Foreign Member of the Royal Society\" class=\"mw-redirect\">ForMemRS<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/British_Academy\" title=\"British Academy\">FBA<\/a> (born February 9, 1943) is an American economist and a professor at <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Columbia_University\" title=\"Columbia University\">Columbia University<\/a>. He is a recipient of the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Memorial_Prize_in_Economic_Sciences\" title=\"Nobel Memorial Prize in Economic Sciences\">Nobel Memorial Prize in Economic Sciences<\/a> (2001) and the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/John_Bates_Clark_Medal\" title=\"John Bates Clark Medal\">John Bates Clark Medal<\/a> (1979). He is a former senior vice president and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/World_Bank_Chief_Economist\" title=\"World Bank Chief Economist\">chief economist<\/a> of the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/World_Bank\" title=\"World Bank\">World Bank<\/a> and is a former member and chairman of the (US president's) <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Council_of_Economic_Advisers\" title=\"Council of Economic Advisers\">Council of Economic Advisers<\/a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Joseph_E._Stiglitz#cite_note-2\"><span>[<\/span>2<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Joseph_E._Stiglitz#cite_note-3\"><span>[<\/span>3<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> He is known for his critical view of the management of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Globalization\" title=\"Globalization\">globalization<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Free_market\" title=\"Free market\">free-market<\/a> economists (whom he calls \"<a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Market_fundamentalism\" title=\"Market fundamentalism\">free market fundamentalists<\/a>\"), and some international institutions like the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/International_Monetary_Fund\" title=\"International Monetary Fund\">International Monetary Fund<\/a> and the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/World_Bank\" title=\"World Bank\">World Bank<\/a>.<\/p><p>In 2000, Stiglitz founded the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Initiative_for_Policy_Dialogue\" title=\"Initiative for Policy Dialogue\">Initiative for Policy Dialogue<\/a> (IPD), a <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Think_tank\" title=\"Think tank\">think tank<\/a> on international development based at Columbia University. He has been a member of the Columbia faculty since 2001, received that university's highest academic rank (<a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/University_Professor_(Columbia)\" title=\"University Professor (Columbia)\" class=\"mw-redirect\">university professor<\/a>) in 2003, and is the co-chair of the university's Committee on Global Thought. He also chairs the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/University_of_Manchester\" title=\"University of Manchester\">University of Manchester<\/a>'s <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Brooks_World_Poverty_Institute\" title=\"Brooks World Poverty Institute\">Brooks World Poverty Institute<\/a> as well as the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Socialist_International\" title=\"Socialist International\">Socialist International<\/a> Commission on Global Financial Issues and is a member of the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Pontifical_Academy_of_Social_Sciences\" title=\"Pontifical Academy of Social Sciences\">Pontifical Academy of Social Sciences<\/a>. Stiglitz has over 40 honorary doctorates and at least eight honorary professorships, as well as an honorary deanship.<sup id=\"cite_ref-cv_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Joseph_E._Stiglitz#cite_note-cv-4\"><span>[<\/span>4<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Joseph_E._Stiglitz#cite_note-5\"><span>[<\/span>5<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Joseph_E._Stiglitz#cite_note-6\"><span>[<\/span>6<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> In 2009 the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/President_of_the_United_Nations_General_Assembly\" title=\"President of the United Nations General Assembly\">President of the United Nations General Assembly<\/a> <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Miguel_d%27Escoto_Brockmann\" title=\"Miguel d'Escoto Brockmann\">Miguel d'Escoto Brockmann<\/a>, appointed Stiglitz as the chairman of the U.N. Commission on Reforms of the International Monetary and Financial System, where he oversaw suggested proposals and commissioned a report on reforming the international monetary and financial system.<sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Joseph_E._Stiglitz#cite_note-7\"><span>[<\/span>7<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> Since 2012 Stiglitz has been the president of the International Economic Association.<sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Joseph_E._Stiglitz#cite_note-8\"><span>[<\/span>8<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> He presided over the organization of the IEA triennial world congress held near the Dead Sea in Jordan in June 2014.<sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Joseph_E._Stiglitz#cite_note-9\"><span>[<\/span>9<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p><p>Based on academic citations, Stiglitz is the 4th most influential economist in the world today,<sup id=\"cite_ref-IDEAS_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Joseph_E._Stiglitz#cite_note-IDEAS-10\"><span>[<\/span>10<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> and in 2011 he was named by <i><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Time_(magazine)\" title=\"Time (magazine)\">Time<\/a><\/i> magazine as one of the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Time_100\" title=\"Time 100\">100 most influential people in the world<\/a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-11\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Joseph_E._Stiglitz#cite_note-11\"><span>[<\/span>11<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> Stiglitz's work focuses on income distribution, asset risk management, corporate governance, and international trade. He is the author of several books, the latest being the best seller, <i>The Great Divide: Unequal Societies and What We Can Do About Them<\/i> (2015).<sup id=\"cite_ref-12\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Joseph_E._Stiglitz#cite_note-12\"><span>[<\/span>12<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p>","name":"Joseph E. Stiglitz","place_of_birth":"Gary, Indiana, USA","place_of_death":null,"text":"Joseph E. Stiglitz , Economics, 2001","year":2001.0}